article.headline: Brown 80, Columbia 56
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Jason Forte scored 20 points and got help from a pair of freshmen as Brown won its first Ivy League home game of the season, 80-56 over Columbia on Friday night. Freshman Damon Huffman scored 15 of his 17 points in the first half when he was 5-for-5 from 3-point range as the Bears (11-15, 4-8 Ivy) took a 44-21 halftime lead. Classmate Keenan Jeppesen hit 7-of-9 shots from the floor and finished with 16 points. John Baumann had 16 points to lead Columbia (12-14, 3-10), which lost its ninth straight. Huffman and Jeppesen scored all the points in a 16-4 run in the first half as Brown pulled ahead 35-15. Huffman connected on three 3-point shots while Jeppesen contributed seven points. Brown held Columbia to 35 percent shooting in the first half. Sam Manhanga scored all of his 10 points in the second half as the Bears led by as many as 25 points, 61-36. Forte also had four steals to increase his career total to 186, one shy of the Brown record set by Mike Waitkus from 1982-86.
